Note:
Comprehensive tests for the IO module
:End Note

Note: Test basic file operations
:End Note

Let test_file be "test_basic.txt"
Let test_content be "Hello, Runa IO Module!"

Note: Test file writing
:End Note
Write test_content to file test_file
Assert file test_file exists is equal to true

Note: Test file reading
:End Note
Let read_content be read file test_file
Assert read_content is equal to test_content

Note: Test file size
:End Note
Let file_size be size of file test_file
Assert file_size is equal to length of test_content

Note: Test file appending
:End Note
Let append_content be "\nAppended content"
Append append_content to file test_file
Let final_content be read file test_file
Assert final_content is equal to test_content plus append_content

Note: Test binary file operations
:End Note
Let binary_file be "test_binary.dat"
Let binary_data be [72, 101, 108, 108, 111]  Note: "Hello" in ASCII
Write binary binary_data to file binary_file
Let read_binary be read binary file binary_file
Assert read_binary is equal to binary_data

Note: Test line-based operations
:End Note
Let lines_file be "test_lines.txt"
Let test_lines be ["Line 1", "Line 2", "Line 3"]
Write lines test_lines to file lines_file
Let read_lines be read lines from file lines_file
Assert read_lines is equal to test_lines

Note: Test file copying and moving
:End Note
Let copy_file be "test_copy.txt"
Copy file from test_file to copy_file
Assert file copy_file exists is equal to true

Let move_file be "test_move.txt"
Move file from copy_file to move_file
Assert file move_file exists is equal to true
Assert file copy_file exists is equal to false

Note: Test file deletion
:End Note
Delete file move_file
Assert file move_file exists is equal to false

Note: Test directory operations
:End Note
Let test_dir be "test_directory"
Create directory test_dir
Assert is directory at test_dir is equal to true

Let nested_dir be "test_directory/nested/subdir"
Create directories nested_dir
Assert is directory at nested_dir is equal to true

Note: Test directory listing
:End Note
Let test_file1 be "test_directory/file1.txt"
Let test_file2 be "test_directory/file2.txt"
Write "File 1" to file test_file1
Write "File 2" to file test_file2

Let files be list files in directory test_dir
Assert length of files is greater than or equal to 2

Let subdirs be list subdirectories in directory test_dir
Assert length of subdirs is greater than or equal to 1

Note: Test path operations
:End Note
Let abs_path be absolute path of test_file
Assert length of abs_path is greater than 0

Let joined_path be join paths ["folder", "subfolder", "file.txt"]
Assert joined_path contains "folder"
Assert joined_path contains "subfolder"
Assert joined_path contains "file.txt"

Let path_parts be split path "/home/user/documents/file.txt"
Assert length of path_parts is greater than 0

Let ext be file extension of "document.pdf"
Assert ext is equal to "pdf"

Let filename be filename of "/path/to/file.txt"
Assert filename is equal to "file.txt"

Let dirname be directory of "/path/to/file.txt"
Assert dirname is equal to "/path/to"

Note: Test system directories
:End Note
Let cwd be current working directory
Assert length of cwd is greater than 0

Let temp_dir be system temporary directory
Assert length of temp_dir is greater than 0

Let home_dir be user home directory
Assert length of home_dir is greater than 0

Note: Test temporary file creation
:End Note
Let temp_file be create temp file with prefix as "runa_test_" and suffix as ".tmp"
Assert file temp_file exists is equal to true
Write "Temporary content" to file temp_file
Delete file temp_file

Let temp_dir be create temp directory with prefix as "runa_test_"
Assert is directory at temp_dir is equal to true
Delete file temp_dir

Note: Test file metadata
:End Note
Let metadata_file be "metadata_test.txt"
Write "Test content" to file metadata_file

Assert is file at metadata_file is equal to true
Assert is directory at metadata_file is equal to false

Let modified_time be last modified time of file metadata_file
Assert modified_time is greater than 0

Let permissions be file permissions of metadata_file
Assert permissions is greater than 0

Note: Test file comparison
:End Note
Let file1 be "compare1.txt"
Let file2 be "compare2.txt"
Let file3 be "compare3.txt"

Write "Same content" to file file1
Write "Same content" to file file2
Write "Different content" to file file3

Assert compare files file1 and file2 is equal to true
Assert compare files file1 and file3 is equal to false

Note: Test file hashing
:End Note
Let hash_file be "hash_test.txt"
Write "Content to hash" to file hash_file
Let hash_value be hash of file hash_file using "md5"
Assert length of hash_value is greater than 0

Note: Test file truncation
:End Note
Let truncate_file be "truncate_test.txt"
Write "This is a long content that will be truncated" to file truncate_file
Truncate file truncate_file to 10 bytes
Let truncated_content be read file truncate_file
Assert length of truncated_content is equal to 10

Note: Test file touch
:End Note
Let touch_file be "touch_test.txt"
Write "Original content" to file touch_file
Let original_time be last modified time of file touch_file
Call sleep with seconds as 1
Touch file touch_file
Let new_time be last modified time of file touch_file
Assert new_time is greater than original_time

Note: Test error handling
:End Note
Try:
    Let content be read file "nonexistent_file.txt"
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Expected error for non-existent file
    :End Note

Try:
    Write "content" to file "/invalid/path/file.txt"
    Assert false  Note: Should not reach here
:End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Expected error for invalid path
    :End Note

Note: Test directory walking
:End Note
Let walk_dir be "walk_test"
Create directories walk_dir
Let subdir1 be "walk_test/subdir1"
Let subdir2 be "walk_test/subdir2"
Create directory subdir1
Create directory subdir2

Let file1 be "walk_test/file1.txt"
Let file2 be "walk_test/subdir1/file2.txt"
Let file3 be "walk_test/subdir2/file3.txt"

Write "File 1" to file file1
Write "File 2" to file file2
Write "File 3" to file file3

Let walked_files be walk directory walk_dir
Assert length of walked_files is greater than 0

Note: Test relative path operations
:End Note
Let base_path be current working directory
Let relative_file be "relative_test.txt"
Write "Relative content" to file relative_file

Let rel_path be relative path from base_path to relative_file
Assert length of rel_path is greater than 0

Note: Test file locking (basic test)
:End Note
Let lock_file be "lock_test.txt"
Write "Locked content" to file lock_file

Try:
    Lock file lock_file
    Note: File should be locked
    :End Note
    Unlock file lock_file
    Note: File should be unlocked
    :End Note
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Locking may not be supported on all systems
    :End Note

Note: Test file compression (basic test)
:End Note
Let compress_source be "compress_source.txt"
Write "Content to compress" to file compress_source

Try:
    Compress file from compress_source to "compressed.gz"
    Assert file "compressed.gz" exists is equal to true
    
    Decompress file from "compressed.gz" to "decompressed.txt"
    Assert file "decompressed.txt" exists is equal to true
    
    Let original be read file compress_source
    Let decompressed be read file "decompressed.txt"
    Assert original is equal to decompressed
Catch Error as e:
    Note: Compression may not be supported on all systems
    :End Note

Note: Cleanup test files
:End Note
Delete file test_file
Delete file binary_file
Delete file lines_file
Delete file metadata_file
Delete file file1
Delete file file2
Delete file file3
Delete file hash_file
Delete file truncate_file
Delete file touch_file
Delete file relative_file
Delete file compress_source
Delete file "compressed.gz"
Delete file "decompressed.txt"

Note: Cleanup test directories
:End Note
Delete file test_dir
Delete file walk_dir

Call print with message as "All IO module tests passed!" 